e=\"text-align: center; border-left: 1px solid #a0a0a0;\">--</td><td style=\"text-align: center; border-left: 1px solid #a0a0a0;\">--</td><td style=\"text-align: center; border-left: 1px solid #a0a0a0;\">--</td><td style=\"text-align: center; border-left: 1px solid #a0a0a0;\">--</td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Notes:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>7, 9, or 11</strong>: Number needed to turn successfully.</li><li><strong>T</strong>: Automatic turn; turns 2d6 Hit Dice of undead.</li><li><strong>D</strong>: Automatic destroy; destroys 2d6 Hit Dice of undead.</li><li><strong>D+</strong>: Automatic destroy; destroys 3d6 Hit Dice of undead.</li></ul><p>An Avenger can turn undead as a cleric of one-third their level, but with a key difference. If the result is \"turn\" or \"destroy,\" the Avenger may instead choose to control the undead. This control lasts for 1 turn per Avenger level—for example, a 17th-level Avenger could maintain control for 17 turns. While controlled, the undead behave as if charmed, obeying the Avenger as if they were allies.</p><p>If a cleric successfully turns or destroys the undead during the control's duration, the effect is immediately broken and cannot be renewed. However, if the control expires naturally, the undead will flee as if turned.</p>",
